The paper focuses on the algorithmic and practical issues related to data/signal processing on graphs, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the analysis and estimation of both deterministic and random data on graphs, which is related to numerical analysis (cs.NA). Additionally, the paper covers topics related to graph theory and graph algorithms, which could fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
